1.title: Hurricane Harvey Special
1.plot: In the Season 3 premiere, Diarra opens up the clinic after Hurricane Harvey pours more than 30 inches of rain on Houston, and the doctors help animals affected by the storm, all while dealing with the personal issues.

2.title: Award Winning Docs
2.plot: The doctors are honored for their contributions to the community. Before the event, they care for a goat with a badly twisted leg; a great dane with a life-threatening condition; and a bulldog rescued from a puppy mill.

3.title: Doctor Dads
3.plot: Dr. Ross starts off the day with a trio of mischievous ferrets suffering from a skin condition; and Bella, a 9-year-old shepherd, is diagnosed with an extremely large tumor and her family is faced with difficult decisions.

4.title: Vegan Cowboys
4.plot: Dr. Blue takes a trip to a vegan cattle ranch to castrate five 1200-pound adult bulls, but tension runs high when bulldozing occurs. Meanwhile, Dr. Ross treats a hen with a rough mating injury; and a young puppy needs a surgery after being hit by a car.

5.title: Dr.Blue Gets Tanked
5.plot: Dr. Blue's love of fish has him wanting a home aquarium. Dr. Ross attempts to diagnose Layla, a Lab with bizarre test results. Dr. Lavigne performs knee surgery on a bulldog. A lamb, headed to the county fair, suddenly has breathing problems.

6.title: Bait n' Switch
6.plot: Dr. Ross deals with six sugar gliders that show off their best moves; Zorro, a one-year-old Chihuahua-mix, shocks Dr. Lavigne with heart trouble not typically seen in a young dog; and the doctors hit the bay on a fishing trip with a client.

7.title: Fly, Miss Thang, Fly
7.plot: Dr. Ross examines a barred owl that was hit by a car; Jamie Bell, a dog who hasn't eaten in days, is hiding a secret; and the docs visit an animal rescue center and get up close with some Texas wildlife.

8.title: Wedding Day Blues
8.plot: Dr. Blue surprises his wife with a romantic wedding-vow renewal in Las Vegas; a schnauzer boarding at the clinic needs medical help from Dr. Lavigne; Dr. Ross treats a very ornery parrot; a senior dog with a recurring eye mass visits Dr. Blue again.

1.title: Hello Houston
1.plot: Houston welcomes veterinarians Dr. Blue, Dr. Ross and Dr. Lavigne. With cases ranging from risky surgeries to diagnosing hungry chameleons, their hands are full. A car accident brings the practice to a halt as one of the doctors faces a long recovery.

2.title: Turnin' Texan
2.plot: Dr. Ross is back at the clinic, but a check-up with a large pet proves to be too much too soon. When pregnant Frenchie goes into early labor, Dr. Lavigne performs an emergency c-section. Dr. Blue plans a Texas outing, to help lift Dr. Ross's spirits.

3.title: No Goats, No Glory
3.plot: While Dr. Blue & Dr. Ross help a client at their goat farm, Dr. Lavigne must save a pup with an obstruction in his intestines and a concerned family waiting. Dr. Blue & Dr. Ross compete in a cook-off to see who is the best grill master.

4.title: The Vet Mobile
4.plot: Dr. Ross buys a mobile unit for community outreach and Dr. Blue enlists his brother to help deck it out. Back at the clinic, Dr. Ross examines an iguana for an abscess and Dr. Lavigne helps a paraplegic dachshund get a new set of wheels.

5.title: Raining Cats, Dogs, and Tigers
5.plot: Flooding has sent Houston into a state of emergency. While the clinic takes in displaced animals, Dr. Blue treats a puppy that has contracted a deadly disease from standing water. Dr. Lavigne and Dr. Ross examine a tiger found wandering in a neighborhood.

6.title: Hope for Hoppy
6.plot: Dr. Ross performs a life-altering surgery on a sweet pup given a second chance at life, while Dr. Lavigne examines a prickly pet. After treating an injured owl, Dr. Blue joins Dr. Ross on pig farm to examine a cute litter of tiny piglets that are sick.

7.title: Training Day
7.plot: Dr. Lavigne must remove tumors from an older dog, while Dr. Ross tries to save a rabbit's foot that's been damaged by a dog attack. Before he can compete with Dr. Ross in a puppy-training competition, Dr. Blue visits farm to castrate an aggressive donkey.

8.title: Lights, Camera, Action!
8.plot: The clock is ticking as Dr. Blue performs an emergency C-section on a mother with two puppies stuck in her uterus, while Dr. Ross and Dr. Lavigne work on pets with serious eye issues. The vets test their on-camera skills to create a video for the clinic.

1.title: Dunk-A-Doctor
1.plot: In the Season 2 premiere, Aubrey treats baby kangaroos and hooks up with the owners of a petting zoo for an event at the clinic to promote animal awareness. Meanwhile, Diarra removes a mass from a beloved dog.

2.title: Not So Easy Riders
2.plot: Aubrey sees a bearded dragon that's laying bad eggs; Michael mulls treatment for a boxer with a tumor on its toe; Diarra's dreams of motorcycle riding with his brother are put on hold by a health scare.

3.title: Hog Wild and Free Home
3.plot: Diarra treats a pig with a taste for household furniture; Michael makes a decision about a mastiff with a toy lodged in its intestines; Aubrey and his wife look forward to moving out of his mother's house and getting a place of their own.

4.title: Litte Dog, Big Problem
4.plot: Dr. Blue uncovers a big problem for a paralyzed Yorkie. Dr. Ross takes care of a pair of roosters involved in a barnyard braw, before joining Dr. Lavigne on a hyena consultation. The Lavigne family hosts a dinner party showcasing Anne's cooking skills.

5.title: Emergency Engine Car
5.plot: Dr. Ross and vet tech Kyerra rush into action to save a stray cat that's been brutally mangled by a car engine. The Ross' move into their new home while Dr. Blue treats a 700lb arthritic pig. Dr. Lavigne sees a rescue Chihuahua with an incredible story.

6.title: California Dreamin'
6.plot: A conference in San Diego has the doctors battling it out to see who will attend. Meanwhile, Aubrey treats a kinkajou that's almost 2 years old.Diarra gets rid of a miniature Doberman pinscher's bad breath.

7.title: Miracle Puppies
7.plot: Diarra needs to act fast when a Rottweiler in labor is rushed into the hospital with two puppies stuck inside her. Later, the three vets ride horseback into town for Houston's biggest rodeo parade.

8.title: Tuskegee Reunion
8.plot: The doctors visit their alma mater, Tuskegee University, for a class reunion. Meanwhile, a Shih Tzu is rushed to the clinic after swallowing a piece of rawhide; and the owner of pit bull with a deformed leg mulls drastic surgery.
